             </h3>
             <p style="padding-left: 22px;">Conjugal rights is a petition filed by a husband or wife as a remedy to restore their rights to cohabiting with the other spouse. The guilty party can be directed to live with the
                  aggrieved party through a decree of restitution of conjugal rights. There are three important requisites to be fulfilled:</p>
             <ul>
                 <li>
                     i.	Spouses must not be staying together.
                 </li>
                 <li>
                     ii.	Withdrawal of a party from the other must have no reasonable ground for such withdrawal.
                 </li>
                 <li>
                     iii.	The aggrieved party must apply for restitution of conjugal rights.
                 </li>
             </ul>   
